    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> fitzgen submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13225#pullrequestreview-4196947993\">PR review</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Thanks @bongjunj! One question below.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 591783156,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1777466373
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> fitzgen created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13225#discussion_r3160988230\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Would it be good enough to eagerly translate CLIF <code>icmp</code> instructions into two Souper instructions: a compare followed by a zero extend? Eg something like this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"WebAssembly\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"c1\">;; CLIF</span>\n<span class=\"err\">v</span><span class=\"mi\">3</span> <span class=\"err\">=</span> <span class=\"err\">icmp</span> <span class=\"err\">eq</span> <span class=\"err\">v</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"err\">,</span> <span class=\"err\">v</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span>\n<span class=\"err\">v</span><span class=\"mi\">4</span> <span class=\"err\">=</span> <span class=\"err\">bor</span> <span class=\"err\">v</span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"err\">,</span> <span class=\"err\">v</span><span class=\"mi\">3</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">;; Souper</span>\n<span class=\"err\">%</span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"err\">:i</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"err\">=</span> <span class=\"err\">eq</span> <span class=\"err\">%</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"err\">,</span> <span class=\"err\">%</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span>\n<span class=\"err\">%</span><span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"err\">:i</span><span class=\"mi\">8</span> <span class=\"err\">=</span> <span class=\"err\">zext</span> <span class=\"err\">%</span><span class=\"mi\">3</span>\n<span class=\"err\">%</span><span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"err\">:i</span><span class=\"mi\">8</span> <span class=\"err\">=</span> <span class=\"err\">or</span> <span class=\"err\">%</span><span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"err\">,</span> <span class=\"err\">%</span><span class=\"mi\">4</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I think this would be a bit simpler and lets us avoid the <code>SouperValue</code> machinery, while also fixing the same set of type mismatch bugs? But I'm not 100% sure on that, so I'm interested in your feedback and whether you considered this approach.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 591783157,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1777466374
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>alexcrichton unassigned alexcrichton from <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13225\">PR #13225 Fix souper harvest</a>.</p>",
